        Official Singles Chart on 3/2/2017

        3 February 2017 - 9 February 2017

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        Nice review Synthesiza! :D
        I might as well post my Ups & Downs here too...
        Ups:
        - Ed Sheeran taking the Top 2 spots again. I consider him to be one of my favourite artists of the decade. The #1 is good & the #2 is great.
        - The Chainsmokers earn their third Top 5 hit! However, I like them a lot more than post people do.
        - Dua Lipa earned her first Top 10 hit & will probably get her second next Friday. 'Be The One' is much better than 'No Lie' though.
        - A decent week for debuts. Best: 'Scared To Be Lonely', Worst: 'T-Shirt'.
        - 'Tilted', 'Move Your Body' & 'Let It Go' are back. Although, other than Sia's song, I don't expect them to stay around for very long.
        - On the albums chart, the 'La La Land' soundtrack hit #1!
        Downs:
        - 'Castle On The Hill' probably won't hit #1. As we've previously discussed, I really want to see a rock song at the top soon for a change.
        - While I'm very pleased to see Ed Sheeran back, I'd like a bit more competition for the top soon. I don't want the charts to get boring like when 'One Dance' was stuck at #1.
        - Stagnant & uninteresting Top 10 in general.
        - 'After The Afterparty', 'Black Beatles' & 'Mercy' all leave the Top 40 & none of these are likely to return; I really liked all of these songs.
        - 'Shed A Light' fell back down this week. Hopefully it can recover.
        - 'Bad & Boujee' is still gaining. It was bad enough seeing 'Juju On Dat Beat' in the lower Top 40 & we really don't need this meme going higher than that either.
        Overall:
        I enjoyed this week a bit more than you did, but yeah, it was nothing too special.

        Ed Sheeran holds the top 2 spots on the Official UK Singles Chart for a fourth straight week, with "Shape of You" at number 1 and "Castle On the Hill" at number 2. "Shape of You" sold 47,000 units and was streamed 8.8 million times this week. In just four weeks the song has sold a total of 306,000 copies and has been streamed 42.9 million times. Ed Sheeran has now matched the record for most consecutive weeks in the top 2 spots by an artist. He now joins Justin Bieber whose singles "Love Yourself" and "Sorry" held number 1 and 2 for four weeks in November, 2015.

        "You Don't Know Me" by Jax Jones (feat RAYE) remains firm at number 3 this week.

        "Run Up" by Major Lazer (feat Partnextdoor and Nicki Minaj) debuts at number 20.

        "Scared to Be Lonely" by Martin Garrix & Dua Lipa debuts at number 23. According to Garrix the song is a follow-up to his 2016-collaboration "In the Name of Love" with Bebe Rexha.

        "Samantha" by Dave & J Hus debuts at number 63.

        My thoughts & observations on the UK charts as always…
        - Ed Sheeran is still at #1 & #2 on the singles chart with ‘Shape Of You’ & ‘Castle On The Hill’ respectively. The former continues to have a solid lead overall; keeping consistent on sales & taking a slight fall in streaming this week (though still dominating both categories by a big margin), but also leading the radio charts for a second consecutive week too. ‘Shape Of You’s performance was also helped by the release of the official video, which was #1 on YouTube trending earlier this week.
        - This week, ‘Shape Of You’ accumulated 47,000 sales & 8.8 million streams. In total, the song has received 306,000 sales & 42.9 million streams. However, the gap between It & ‘Castle On The Hill’ did close slightly this week.
        - Although it probably won’t happen, I still really hope ‘Castle On The Hill’ can get to #1, as it would be awesome to see rock back atop the UK charts. As for Ed taking the Top 2 spots again, I’m fine with that for now as both songs are good, but I’d like to see some competition challenging him soon though. Ed also released his tour tickets at 10am yesterday morning & they had sold out across the country in just 40 minutes.
        - Dua Lipa has another big week with her songs; she earns her first Top 10 hit with ‘No Lie’ (11-10). It just became Sean Paul’s 12th Top 10 in the main chart! Another reason why 2017 could be a very successful year for Dua Lipa; ‘No Lie’ & ‘Be The One’ take the #1 & #2 spots on overall trending this week, in that order.
        - ‘Be The One’ leaps 21-11 on the singles chart this week, but could also go Top 10 next week. This was the first ever song I heard from her & I would easily still call It my favourite. I’m pleased that her record label decided to release it in the UK again. It’s performing well on both sales & radio, but really needs more streaming support.
        - ZAYN & Taylor Swift’s ‘I Don’t Wanna Live Forever’ rises to a new peak as It ascends 18-13 today. This is thanks to the release of the official video & big climbs in sales. ‘Fifty Shades Darker’ will be released next Friday, which is why I could see this song going Top 10 on the next chart.
        - The highest debuting song of the week is ‘Run Up’ by Major Lazer ft PARTYNEXTDOOR & Nicki Minaj, starting at #20. Including this, the latter act now has 24 Top 40 entries (including leads & features). This is the official follow-up to the huge former #1, ‘Cold Water’ & I’m certainly impressed! While the tropical beat is becoming generic on the radio, it still makes me think of summer & Nicki Minaj’s rap verse is much better than I expected it to be.
        - More on Dua Lipa, as ‘Scared To Be Lonely’ enters at #23 this week. It becomes Martin Garrix’s sixth Top 40 appearance in the UK & Dua’s fifth. It’s no ‘In The Name Of Love’, but it’s a still an awesome collaboration & I can definitely see it growing on me. Addictive drop & awesome vocals.
        - Rag’n’Bone Man earns his second Top 40 with the follow-up to ‘Human’, called ‘Skin’ (debuting at #35). Like his previous big hit, the rock sound & soulful vocals remain & I think it’s fine at first listen. This will very likely be climbing the Top 40 over the next couple of weeks, ‘Skin’ also acts as the second single from Rag’n’Bone Man’s debut album, ‘Human’, which is due to be released next Friday.
        - It was a shame that neither ‘Play That Song’ by Train nor ‘So Good’ by Zara Larsson ft Ty Dolla $ign entered the Top 40, but I think both (especially the former) will next week. Other songs that could also possibly reach the Top 40 include: ‘Big For Your Boots’ by Stormzy, ‘Safe Inside’ by James Arthur, ‘Talking To You’ by Izzy Bizu, ‘Not In Love’ by M.O. ft Kent Jones, ‘Believer’ by Imagine Dragons & ‘Digital Love’ by Digital Farm Animals ft Hailee Steinfeld.
        - Finally, the upper region of the albums chart: the ‘La La Land’ motion picture cast recording climbs 2-1 following its 14 Oscar nominations. The rest of the Top 5 is: ‘Classic House’ by Pete Tong (1-2), ‘Glory Days’ by Little Mix (stationary at #3), ‘x’ by Ed Sheeran (10-4) & ‘All These Countless Nights’ by Deaf Havana (debuts at #5).
        - Thank you all for reading & have a great weekend! :)
